data.chText: （坐着时的）大腿部
data.enText: the top part of your legs that forms a flat surface when you are sitting down

data.chText: 只有一个座位，你只好坐在我腿上了。
data.enText: There's only one seat so you'll have to sit on my lap .

data.chText: 她双手放在大腿上坐着。
data.enText: She sat with her hands in her lap .

data.chText: （跑道等的）一圈
data.enText: one journey from the beginning to the end of a track used for running, etc.

data.chText: 在纪录上最快的一圈
data.enText: the fastest lap on record

data.chText: 她跑完六圈了。
data.enText: She has completed six laps.

data.chText: 他在最后一圈被超过。
data.enText: He was overtaken on the final lap.

data.chText: 绕场一周欢庆胜利
data.enText: to do a lap of honour (= go around the track again to celebrate winning)

data.chText: 绕场一周庆祝胜利
data.enText: to do a victory lap

data.chText: （行程或工作中的）一段，环节
data.enText: a section of a journey, or of a piece of work, etc.

data.chText: 他们踏上环游世界的第一段行程。
data.enText: They're off on the first lap of their round-the-world tour.

data.chText: 我们接近完工了，正在处理最后的一部分工作。
data.enText: We've nearly finished. We're on the last lap .
drop/dump sth in sb's lap

data.chText: 把（某事）推给他人负责
data.enText: to make sth the responsibility of another person

data.chText: 他们把问题断然给我推了回来。
data.enText: They dropped the problem firmly back in my lap.
sth drops/falls into sb's lap

data.chText: （毫不费劲地）得到做称心事的机会；赐良机
data.enText: somebody has the opportunity to do sth pleasant without having made any effort

data.chText: 我没费劲就找到了梦寐以求的工作。
data.enText: My dream job just fell into my lap.
in the lap of the gods

data.chText: 由神掌管；结果难以预料；非人力所能左右
data.enText: if the result of sth is in the lap of the gods , you do not know what will happen because it depends on luck or things you cannot control
in the lap of luxury

data.chText: 生活优裕；养尊处优
data.enText: in easy, comfortable conditions, and enjoying the advantages of being rich

data.chText: （轻柔而有规律地）拍打
data.enText: to touch sth gently and regularly, often making a soft sound

data.chText: 波浪轻轻地拍打着我们的脚。
data.enText: The waves lapped around our feet.

data.chText: 水轻轻拍打船帮的声音
data.enText: the sound of water lapping against the boat

data.chText: 舔食；舔着喝
data.enText: to drink sth with quick movements of the tongue

data.chText: 领先一圈（或数圈）
data.enText: to pass another runner on a track who is one or more laps behind you
lap sth↔up

data.chText: （不加考虑地）乐于接受
data.enText: to accept or receive sth with great enjoyment, without thinking about whether it is good, true or sincere

data.chText: 这是一部很糟糕的电影，可各地的观众却趋之若鹜。
data.enText: It's a terrible movie but audiences everywhere are lapping it up.

data.chText: 什么恭维话她都照单全收。
data.enText: She simply lapped up all the compliments.

data.chText: 开怀畅饮
data.enText: to drink all of sth with great enjoyment

data.chText: 牛犊把那桶牛奶津津有味地喝光了。
data.enText: The calf lapped up the bucket of milk.

trans: 轻信；照单全收；欣然接受

example: the dog's laps were warm and wet
he drove an extra lap just for insurance

tr: a flap that lies over another part
example: the lap of the shingles should be at least ten inches

tr: the part of a piece of clothing that covers the thighs
example: his lap was covered with food stains

tr: the upper side of the thighs of a seated person
example: he picked up the little girl and plopped her down in his lap

tr: an area of control or responsibility
example: the job fell right in my lap
The cat lapped up the milk
the cub licked the milk from its mother's breast

tr: move with or cause to move with a whistling or hissing sound
example: The bubbles swoshed around in the glass

tr: lie partly over or alongside of something or of one another

value.def: If you have something on your lap when you are sitting down, it is on top of your legs and near to your body.

example.ex: She waited quietly with her hands in her lap...
example.tran: 她双手放在腿上静静等候。

example.ex: Hugh glanced at the child on her mother's lap.
example.tran: 休瞥了一眼坐在她妈妈膝上的小女孩。

value.def: In a race, a competitor completes a lap when they have gone round a course once.

example.ex: On lap two, Baker edged forward.
example.tran: 第二圈时，贝克悄然赶了上去。

value.def: In a race, if you lap another competitor, you go past them while they are still on the previous lap.

example.ex: He was caught out while lapping a slower rider.
example.tran: 他在套圈超越一位落后的车手时出了错。

value.def: A lap of a long journey is one part of it, between two points where you stop.

example.ex: I had thought we might travel as far as Oak Valley, but we only managed the first lap of the journey.
example.tran: 我原以为我们最远能到达橡树谷，结果只走完了第一段路程。

value.def: When water laps against something such as the shore or the side of a boat, it touches it gently and makes a soft sound.

example.ex: ...the water that lapped against the pillars of the boathouse...
example.tran: 轻拍着船屋支柱的海水

example.ex: With a rising tide the water was lapping at his chin before rescuers arrived...
example.tran: 救援人员到达时上涨的潮水已经淹到了他的下巴。

example.ex: The building was right on the river and the water lapped the walls.
example.tran: 建筑物就矗立在水中，河水轻轻拍打着墙壁。

example.ex: The only sound was the lapping of the waves.

value.def: When an animal laps a drink, it uses short quick movements of its tongue to take liquid up into its mouth.

example.ex: The cat lapped milk from a dish.
She poured some water into a plastic bowl. Faust, her Great Dane, lapped it up with relish.
example.tran: 她往一个塑料碗里倒了一些水，她的大丹犬福斯特便美滋滋地舔起来。

value.def: If you say that a situation is in the lap of the gods, you mean that its success or failure depends entirely on luck or on things that are outside your control.

example.ex: They had to stop the operation, so at that stage my life was in the lap of the gods.
example.tran: 他们不得不停止手术，所以那时的我只能听天由命。

value.tran: （成败）难以预料，非人力所能左右

value.def: If you say that someone lives in the lap of luxury, you mean that they live in conditions of great comfort and wealth.

example.ex: We don't live in the lap of luxury, but we're comfortable.
example.tran: 我们的生活虽然并非锦衣玉食，也算是衣食无忧。
